<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do I book a service and what information do you need?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "You can book via phone, email, or our website contact form. Please provide: Type of service required (carpet, upholstery, or exterior cleaning), approximate area size or number of rooms/items, type and age of materials/surfaces, any specific stains or problem areas, and your location for travel time estimation. Final pricing may be adjusted after on-site inspection if actual conditions differ significantly from initial description."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "What are your cancellation policies?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Cancellation charges apply: 48+ hours notice - No charge. 24-48 hours notice - 50% of quoted service price. Less than 24 hours or no access - Full service charge. We require safe, unobstructed access at the scheduled time. Failure to provide access will be treated as a late cancellation."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "What payment methods do you accept?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Payment is due in full upon completion of service, before our technicians leave the premises. Accepted methods: Cash, Bank Transfer, and Debit/Credit Cards. Late payments may incur interest charges and recovery costs."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "Are you insured?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, we carry full Public Liability Insurance. Insurance certificates are available on request. Any damage claims must be reported in writing within 24 hours of service completion. Claims reported after this period will not be accepted."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "How often should I have my carpets cleaned?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Recommended frequency depends on several factors: Heavy traffic households - Every 6-9 months. Average households - Every 12-18 months. Low traffic/guest areas - Every 18-24 months. With pets/children - Consider more frequent cleaning (every 4-6 months). Regular professional cleaning extends carpet life and maintains appearance."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you guarantee complete stain removal?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "We cannot guarantee complete removal of all stains or discolouration. Stain removal success depends on: type of stain (coffee, wine, ink, pet accidents, etc.), age of the stain, fibre composition and dye stability, previous cleaning attempts, and colourfastness of materials. We will make every effort to achieve the best possible results, but some soiling may be permanent."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does it take for carpets to dry?",
