        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Carpets will be left damp after cleaning. Typical drying times are 4-12 hours depending on: material type and thickness (wool vs synthetic), room temperature and humidity levels, ventilation and air circulation, weather conditions, and underlay type. Keep furniture off damp carpets until completely dry to prevent re-soiling, mould growth, and compression marks."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "What should I do before you arrive?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Before Service: Remove breakables and valuables from cleaning areas, identify and disclose all stains/areas of concern, secure pets and children away from work areas, move small furniture if possible (we can move light furniture), and vacuum thoroughly if possible. After Service: Ensure adequate ventilation for drying, keep foot traffic off damp carpets, replace furniture only when completely dry (use protective pads), and report any concerns immediately to the technician."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "Are your cleaning products safe?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, we use professional-grade, environmentally responsible cleaning solutions. However, we recommend keeping pets and children away until surfaces are completely dry. Individuals with chemical sensitivities should avoid the area during cleaning and until dry. We always test for colourfastness before proceeding. If you have specific allergies or sensitivities, please inform us before we begin."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "What surfaces can you clean with jet washing?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "We can clean various exterior surfaces including: concrete driveways and patios, block paving and stone surfaces, decking and wooden surfaces, brickwork and render, fences and gates, gutters and fascias, paths and walkways, and walls and boundary walls. Some surfaces may require specific treatments or lower pressure settings."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "Will jet washing damage my surfaces?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "We use professional equipment with adjustable pressure settings and appropriate techniques for each surface type. We assess surface condition before starting. Older or weakened surfaces may require special care. We cannot be responsible for pre-existing weaknesses that become apparent after cleaning. Loose pointing, crumbling mortar, or deteriorating surfaces should be reported before service."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you remove oil stains and biological growth?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, we can effectively treat and remove: oil and grease stains, algae, moss, and lichen, mould and mildew, general dirt and grime buildup, and rust stains (where appropriate). Some deeply ingrained or aged stains may not be completely removable. We will advise on likely outcomes during inspection."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "What do I need to prepare for jet washing?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Before we arrive, please: ensure clear access to the area, move vehicles, garden furniture, and potted plants, keep windows and doors closed in the work area, provide access to an outdoor water supply if needed, secure pets away from the work area, and identify any fragile or special surfaces. You do not need to be present if access arrangements are made in advance."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "How often should I have exterior cleaning done?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Recommended frequency depends on: Driveways/Patios - Every 12-24 months. Decking - Every 6-12 months (may need treatment afterwards). Walls/Fences - Every 18-36 months. Gutters - Annually (especially before winter). Areas with heavy shade, moisture, or tree cover may require more frequent cleaning."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "What if I'm not satisfied with the service?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Step 1: Notify the technician immediately before they leave so concerns can be addressed on-site. Step 2: If unresolved, email info@mvmcleaning.co.uk within 24 hours with details and photos. Step 3: We will review your concern and propose a resolution within 48 hours. Claims for damage must be reported in writing within 24 hours of service completion."
      }
    },
    {
      "@@type": "Question",
      "name": "What are my responsibilities if damage occurs?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Our liability is limited to the cost of the service provided. We are not liable for: pre-existing conditions or material weaknesses, improper installations or repairs, damage caused by failure to follow aftercare instructions, colour loss or bleeding on non-colourfast materials, and normal wear and tear. We always test materials where possible and advise on potential risks before proceeding."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

